{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DJ9pdsPkWMFrTsHTKaw8xL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Optional;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→import org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;\n     6→import org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor;\n     7→import org.mockito.junit.jupiter.MockitoExtension;\n     8→import org.mockito.Mock;\n     9→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    10→import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;\n    11→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean;\n    12→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    13→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.LeagueRepository;\n    14→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.PlayerRepository;\n    15→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.TeamRepository;\n    16→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.League;\n    17→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Player;\n    18→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.SummerLeague;\n    19→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Team;\n    20→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.WinterLeague;\n    21→\n    22→@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)\n    23→class RequestBeanUnitTest {\n    24→\n    25→  @Mock PlayerRepository playerRepository;\n    26→  @Mock TeamRepository teamRepository;\n    27→  @Mock LeagueRepository leagueRepository;\n    28→\n    29→  @Test\n    30→  void createLeagueChoosesSeasonType() {\n    31→    RequestBean bean = new RequestBean(playerRepository, teamRepository, leagueRepository);\n    32→\n    33→    bean.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\",\"Name\",\"soccer\"));\n    34→    ArgumentCaptor<League> cap1 = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(League.class);\n    35→    verify(leagueRepository).save(cap1.capture());\n    36→    assertTrue(cap1.getValue() instanceof SummerLeague);\n    37→\n    38→    reset(leagueRepository);\n    39→    bean.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L2\",\"Name\",\"hockey\"));\n    40→    ArgumentCaptor<League> cap2 = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(League.class);\n    41→    verify(leagueRepository).save(cap2.capture());\n    42→    assertTrue(cap2.getValue() instanceof WinterLeague);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Test\n    46→  void addPlayerLinksAndSavesTeam() {\n    47→    RequestBean bean = new RequestBean(playerRepository, teamRepository, leagueRepository);\n    48→    Player p = new Player(\"P1\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100);\n    49→    Team t = new Team(\"T1\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\");\n    50→    when(playerRepository.findById(\"P1\")).thenReturn(Optional.of(p));\n    51→    when(teamRepository.findById(\"T1\")).thenReturn(Optional.of(t));\n    52→\n    53→    bean.addPlayer(\"P1\",\"T1\");\n    54→\n    55→    verify(teamRepository).save(t);\n    56→    assertTrue(t.getPlayers().contains(p));\n    57→    assertTrue(p.getTeams().contains(t));\n    58→  }\n    59→}\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a37b03b-5080-41c1-93e0-db6136171128","uuid":"eb77a980-ccba-4f50-86df-59c8327e5485"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GPfFaXuZDKL4G1fbKpAYun","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     6→import org.springframework.test.annotation.DirtiesContext;\n     7→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     9→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    10→\n    11→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    12→\n    13→@SpringBootTest\n    14→@DirtiesContext(classMode = DirtiesContext.ClassMode.AFTER_EACH_TEST_METHOD)\n    15→class RequestCrudIT {\n    16→\n    17→  @Autowired\n    18→  Request request;\n    19→\n    20→  @Test\n    21→  void leagueTeamPlayerCrud() {\n    22→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"Lx\",\"LX\",\"soccer\"));\n    23→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"Tx\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"Lx\");\n    24→    request.createPlayer(\"Px\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100.0);\n    25→    request.addPlayer(\"Px\",\"Tx\");\n    26→\n    27→    assertEquals(1, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"Tx\").size());\n    28→    assertNotNull(request.getTeam(\"Tx\"));\n    29→    assertNotNull(request.getLeague(\"Lx\"));\n    30→\n    31→    request.removeTeam(\"Tx\");\n    32→    assertEquals(0, request.getTeamsOfLeague(\"Lx\").size());\n    33→    assertEquals(0, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"Tx\").size());\n    34→\n    35→    request.removeLeague(\"Lx\");\n    36→    assertNull(request.getLeague(\"Lx\"));\n    37→\n    38→    request.removePlayer(\"Px\");\n    39→    assertNull(request.getPlayer(\"Px\"));\n    40→    assertEquals(0, request.getAllPlayers().size());\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a37b03b-5080-41c1-93e0-db6136171128","uuid":"c42991a5-51f7-48e0-8c80-9965d207ddaa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CT9wnAggjm2vny5TJtYQUe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     6→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     7→import org.springframework.test.annotation.DirtiesContext;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     9→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    10→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    11→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    12→\n    13→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    14→\n    15→@SpringBootTest\n    16→@DirtiesContext(classMode = DirtiesContext.ClassMode.AFTER_EACH_TEST_METHOD)\n    17→class RequestQueriesIT {\n    18→\n    19→  @Autowired\n    20→  Request request;\n    21→\n    22→  @Test\n    23→  void queryScenarios() {\n    24→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"Lq\",\"Summer\",\"soccer\"));\n    25→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"Tq\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"Lq\");\n    26→    request.createPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100);\n    27→    request.createPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Bob\",\"Goalie\",120);\n    28→    request.createPlayer(\"Pz\",\"Zed\",\"Forward\",90);\n    29→    request.addPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Tq\");\n    30→    request.addPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Tq\");\n    31→\n    32→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByPosition(\"Forward\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pz\")));\n    33→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pb\"), ids(request.getPlayersByHigherSalary(\"Alice\")));\n    34→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersBySalaryRange(95,110)));\n    35→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByLeagueId(\"Lq\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    36→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersBySport(\"soccer\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    37→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByCity(\"Austin\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    38→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersNotOnTeam()).contains(\"Pz\"));\n    39→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersByPositionAndName(\"Forward\",\"Alice\")));\n    40→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Lq\"), request.getLeaguesOfPlayer(\"Pa\").stream().map(LeagueDetails::getId).toList());\n    41→    assertTrue(request.getSportsOfPlayer(\"Pa\").contains(\"soccer\"));\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private static List<String> ids(List<PlayerDetails> list) {\n    45→    return list.stream().map(PlayerDetails::getId).toList();\n    46→  }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a37b03b-5080-41c1-93e0-db6136171128","uuid":"9860e9ea-5f5b-4ff1-992d-c99ab19014ff"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NxyReDBZSE6keZdRFYUgY3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     6→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     7→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n     9→\n    10→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\n    11→\n    12→@SpringBootTest\n    13→class RequestSmokeTest {\n    14→\n    15→  @Autowired\n    16→  Request request;\n    17→\n    18→  @Test\n    19→  void roundTrip() {\n    20→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\",\"Summer Fun\",\"soccer\"));\n    21→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T1\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"L1\");\n    22→    request.createPlayer(\"P1\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100000);\n    23→    request.addPlayer(\"P1\",\"T1\");\n    24→    assertEquals(1, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"T1\").size());\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a37b03b-5080-41c1-93e0-db6136171128","uuid":"34dffe00-af1b-4d1a-94d1-b56dfc0af316"}
